.SH "NAME"
jome \- a keyboard centric desktop emoji picker
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.nf
\fBjome\fP [\fB\-f\fP \f(CRcp\fP [\fB\-p\fP \fIPREFIX\fP]] [\fB\-n\fP] [\fB\-V\fP] [\fB\-t\fP (\fBL\fP | \fBML\fP | \fBM\fP | \fBMD\fP | \fBD\fP)]
     [\fB\-c\fP \fICMD\fP] [\fB\-b\fP] [\fB\-q\fP | \fB\-s\fP \fINAME\fP]
     [\fB\-d\fP] [\fB\-C\fP] [\fB\-L\fP] [\fB\-R\fP] [\fB\-k\fP]
     [\fB\-w\fP (\fB16\fP | \fB24\fP | \fB32\fP | \fB40\fP | \fB48\fP)] [\fB\-P\fP] [\fB\-H\fP \fICOUNT\fP]
.fi
.br
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
\fBjome\fP (joh¬∑mee) is a keyboard centric emoji picker desktop
application.
.sp
jome\(cqs sole purpose is to help you \fIpick\fP an emoji. In other words,
it doesn\(cqt really care what you do with the chosen emoji afterwards:
you can leverage tools such as \fBxdotool\fP(1) to \(lqtype\(rq it or
\fBxsel\fP(1) to copy it to the clipboard. See the
\(lqType the accepted emoji\(rq section below and the \fB\-c\fP\~option for
a starting point.
.sp
When you accept an emoji (with the keyboard or with the mouse), jome
prints the UTF\-8 emoji or the Unicode codepoints (see the \fB\-f\fP
option), with an optional prefix (see the \fB\-p\fP\~option) for each
codepoint, to the standard output.
.sp
Additionally, jome can:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Copy the UTF\-8 emoji or the Unicode codepoints to the clipboard.
.sp
See the \fB\-b\fP\~option.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Execute a custom command which sends the UTF\-8 emoji or the Unicode
codepoints, with an optional prefix for each codepoint, as its last
argument(s).
.sp
See the \fB\-c\fP\~option.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Send the UTF\-8 emoji or the Unicode codepoints, with an optional
prefix for each codepoint, in response to a client which requested
picking an emoji.
.sp
See the \(lqServer mode\(rq section below.
.RE
.sp
If you close the window (you can press \fBEscape\fP or \fBCtrl\fP+\fBC\fP to
do this), then jome prints nothing to the standard output, executes
nothing, and exits with status\~1.
.sp
If you don\(cqt start jome in server mode (\fB\-s\fP\~option) and you
don\(cqt specify the \fB\-q\fP\~option, then jome immediately exits
with status\~0 after you accept an emoji or close the window.
.SS "Graphical interface"
.sp
There are four sections:
.sp
Find box (top)
.RS 4
Input box where you can type a query to find emojis.
.RE
.sp
Emoji grid
.RS 4
All emojis (with an empty find box) or find results.
.sp
When there\(cqs at least one emoji, there\(cqs always a selected emoji with a
square box around it.
.sp
Click an emoji to accept it. Press \fBShift\fP when clicking to not print
VS\-16 codepoints (see the \fB\-V\fP\~option).
.sp
Hover an emoji to update the bottom emoji info text temporarily.
.sp
Make the background behind emojis dark with the \fB\-d\fP\~option.
.sp
Hide the category labels with the \fB\-L\fP\~option.
.sp
Hide the \(lqRecent\(rq category with the \fB\-R\fP\~option.
.RE
.sp
Category list (right)
.RS 4
List of available categories.
.sp
When all emojis are viewed (the find box is empty), click a category
name to scroll to this emoji category.
.sp
The first category, \(lqRecent\(rq, is a special category with the recently
accepted emojis.
.sp
Override the maximum number of recently accepted emojis with
the \fB\-H\fP\~option.
.sp
Hide the \(lqRecent\(rq category with the \fB\-R\fP\~option.
.sp
Hide the whole category list with the \fB\-C\fP\~option.
.RE
.sp
Emoji info text (bottom)
.RS 4
Name, Unicode codepoints, Emoji standard version, and keywords of
the selected or hovered emoji.
.sp
Hide the keyword list with the \fB\-k\fP\~option.
.RE
.SS "Find emojis"
.sp
The power of jome is its \fIfind box\fP (top).
.sp
When you launch jome, the find box is focused, and it should stay
focused unless you browse emojis manually with the intention of
accepting one with the mouse.
.sp
The format of a query is one of:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\fITERMS\fP
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\fICAT\fP/
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\fICAT\fP/\fITERMS\fP
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\fICODEPOINT\fP
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\fICAT\fP/\fICODEPOINT\fP
.RE
.sp
where:
.sp
\fICAT\fP
.RS 4
Partial name of categories in which to find.
.RE
.sp
\fITERMS\fP
.RS 4
Space\-separated list of search terms.
.sp
For an emoji to be part of the results, its name and keywords
must contain ALL the searched terms.
.RE
.sp
\fICODEPOINT\fP
.RS 4
A single Unicode codepoint using the standard \fBU\fP+\fIABCD\fP
notation.
.RE
.sp
Everything is case\-insensitive.
.SS "Select and accept an emoji"
.sp
To select an emoji, use the following keys:
.sp
\fB‚Üê\fP, \fB‚Üí\fP, \fB‚Üë\fP, \fB‚Üì\fP
.RS 4
Go left/right/up/down.
.RE
.sp
\fBCtrl\fP+\fB‚Üê\fP, \fBCtrl\fP+\fB‚Üí\fP
.RS 4
Go left/right five emojis.
.RE
.sp
\fBPage ‚Üë\fP, \fBPage ‚Üì\fP
.RS 4
Go up/down ten rows.
.RE
.sp
\fBHome\fP
.RS 4
Go to the first emoji.
.RE
.sp
\fBEnd\fP
.RS 4
Go to the last emoji.
.RE
.sp
To accept the selected emoji, press:
.sp
\fBEnter\fP
.RS 4
Accept the selected emoji with, if applicable:
.sp
Without the \fB\-t\fP option
.RS 4
No skin tone (\(lqyellow\(rq).
.RE
.sp
With the \fB\-t\fP option
.RS 4
The default skin tone (value of \fB\-t\fP).
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBShift\fP+\fBEnter\fP
.RS 4
Like \fBEnter\fP, but do not print VS\-16 codepoints.
.sp
See the \fB\-V\fP option option.
.RE
.sp
\fBF1\fP to \fBF5\fP
.RS 4
If the selected emoji supports skin tones, accept the selected emoji
with a light, medium\-light, medium, medium\-dark, or dark skin tone,
overriding the \fB\-t\fP option (if any).
.RE
.sp
\fBShift\fP+\fBF1\fP to \fBShift\fP+\fBF5\fP
.RS 4
Like \fBF1\fP to \fBF5\fP, but do not print VS\-16 codepoints.
.sp
See the \fB\-V\fP option option.
.RE
.sp
To cancel, press \fBEscape\fP or \fBCtrl\fP+\fBC\fP, or close the
window.
.SS "Go to Emojipedia page"
.sp
To go to the \c
.URL "https://emojipedia.org/" "Emojipedia" ""
page of the selected
emoji, press \fBF12\fP.
.sp
To go to the Emojipedia page of any emoji with the mouse, right\-click it
and click \(lqGo to Emojipedia page\(rq.
.SS "User\-defined emoji keywords"
.sp
You can either replace or augment the built\-in list of keywords which
jome searches when you find emojis.
.sp
To set user\-defined keywords, create an \fBemojis.json\fP file within
\fB~/.config/jome/\fP.
.sp
\fBemojis.json\fP must contain a JSON object where keys are emojis and
values are objects. Each value may contain one of:
.sp
\fBkeywords\fP
.RS 4
An array of keywords which replaces the built\-in keywords entirely
for this emoji.
.RE
.sp
\fBextra\-keywords\fP
.RS 4
An array of keywords which augments either the built\-in keywords or
the keywords of the keywords entry for this emoji.
.RE
.sp
Example:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
{
  "üçÅ": {
    "extra\-keywords": ["canada", "laurentides"]
  },
  "üòÉ": {
    "keywords": ["yay", "hourra"]
  },
  "üö¨": {
    "extra\-keywords": ["claude poirier"]
  },
  "ü´ö": {
    "extra\-keywords": ["canada dry", "martin deschamps"]
  }
}
.fam
.fi
