.SH "OPTIONS"
.SS "Output"
.sp
\fB\-f\fP \fIFMT\fP
.RS 4
Set the output format to \fIFMT\fP:
.sp
\fButf\-8\fP (default)
.RS 4
UTF\-8 emoji.
.RE
.sp
\fBcp\fP
.RS 4
Space\-separated Unicode codepoints (hexadecimal).
.sp
Example: \fB1f645 200d 2642 fe0f\fP
.sp
Prepend a prefix to each codepoint with the \fB\-p\fP\~option.
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fB\-p\fP \fIPREFIX\fP
.RS 4
Set the prefix to be prepended to each Unicode codepoint with
\fB\-f\fP\~\fBcp\fP.
.sp
For example, with \fB\-f\fP\~\fBcp\fP and \fB\-p\fP\~\fBU+\fP:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
U+1f645 U+200d U+2642 U+fe0f
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\fB\-n\fP
.RS 4
Do not print a newline after printing the emoji or codepoints.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-V\fP
.RS 4
Do not print
\c
.URL "https://emojipedia.org/variation\-selector\-16" "Variation Selector\-16"
(VS\-16) codepoints.
.sp
VS\-16 is a suffix codepoint which specifies that the preceding character
should be displayed with emoji presentation. For example, ‚ô• (which
predates Unicode emojis) followed with VS\-16 becomes a red heart.
.sp
There are applications/fonts which don\(cqt like VS\-16.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-t\fP \fITONE\fP
.RS 4
Set the default skin tone to \fITONE\fP instead of none:
.sp
\fBL\fP
.RS 4
Light.
.RE
.sp
\fBML\fP
.RS 4
Medium\-light.
.RE
.sp
\fBM\fP
.RS 4
Medium.
.RE
.sp
\fBMD\fP
.RS 4
Medium\-dark.
.RE
.sp
\fBD\fP
.RS 4
Dark.
.RE
.sp
The \fBF1\fP to \fBF5\fP keys still acept an emoji with a
specific skin tone.
.RE
.SS "Action"
.sp
\fB\-c\fP \fICMD\fP
.RS 4
When you accept an emoji, execute the command \fICMD\fP 20\~ms
after closing the jome window.
.sp
jome interprets \fICMD\fP like a shell does, so you can have arguments
too.
.sp
\fICMD\fP receives the UTF\-8 emoji or the Unicode codepoints (depending on
the \fB\-f\fP option) with their optional prefix as its last argument(s).
.sp
Examples with xdotool:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
$ jome \-c \*(Aqxdotool type\*(Aq
$ jome \-f cp \-p U \-c \*(Aqxdotool key \-\-delay 20\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.RE
.sp
\fB\-b\fP
.RS 4
When you accept an emoji, copy the UTF\-8 emoji or the Unicode
codepoints (depending on the \fB\-f\fP\~option) to the clipboard.
.if n .sp
.RS 4
.it 1 an-trap
.nr an-no-space-flag 1
.nr an-break-flag 1
.br
.ps +1
.B Warning
.ps -1
.br
.sp
This uses \fBQClipboard\fP and is known not to always work,
depending on your window manager.
.sp .5v
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fB\-q\fP
.RS 4
Do not quit when you accept an emoji.
.sp
By default, when you accept an emoji (with the keyboard or with the
mouse), jome:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 1.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP " 1." 4.2
.\}
Prints the accept emoji or its codepoints to the standard output.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 2.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP " 2." 4.2
.\}
Hides its window.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 3.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP " 3." 4.2
.\}
\fBOptional\fP: Copies the accept emoji/codepoints to the clipboard
(see the \fB\-b\fP\~option).
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 4.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP " 4." 4.2
.\}
\fBOptional\fP: Executes a command (see the \fB\-c\fP\~option)
after 20\~ms.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 5.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP " 5." 4.2
.\}
If not running in server mode, quits (see the \fB\-s\fP option).
.RE
.sp
With the \fB\-q\fP option, jome doesn\(cqt hide its window and doesn\(cqt quit
when you accept an emoji so that you can make it print multiple emojis
and/or execute a command multiple time with multiple emojis without
restarting the application.
.sp
You cannot specify the \fB\-q\fP and \fB\-s\fP options together.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-s\fP \fINAME\fP
.RS 4
Start jome in server mode and set the server name to \fINAME\fP.
.sp
On Unix, this creates the socket file \fB/tmp/\fP\fINAME\fP which must NOT
exist before you start jome.
.sp
You cannot specify the \fB\-s\fP and \fB\-q\fP options together.
.RE
.SS "User interface"
.sp
\fB\-d\fP
.RS 4
Use a dark background for emojis.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-C\fP
.RS 4
Hide the category list.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-L\fP
.RS 4
Hide the category labels in the emoji grid.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-R\fP
.RS 4
Hide the \(lqRecent\(rq category.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-k\fP
.RS 4
Hide the keyword list.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-w\fP \fIWIDTH\fP
.RS 4
Set the width of individual emojis to \fIWIDTH\fP pixels, amongst
16, 24, 32 (default), 40, or\~48.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-P\fP \fIPERIOD\fP
.RS 4
Set the flashing period of the selection box to \fIPERIOD\fP\~ms
(greater than or equal to\~32).
.sp
The selection box doesn\(cqt flash by default.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-H\fP \fICOUNT\fP
.RS 4
Set the maximum number of recently accepted emojis to \fICOUNT\fP
instead of\~30.
.RE
